author: Special to syracuse.com
title: Outlaw 200 Weekend gets started at Fulton Speedway
text:
By Dick O'Brien
Fulton Speedway's 30th annual Outlaw 200 Weekend got underway Friday night with more than 200 cars packing the pit area at the one-third-mile oval on Route 57.
A field of 82 sportsman cars required eight qualifying heats and four consolation events to set a field for the division's 50-lap main event Saturday.
The headline race is Saturday night's 200-lap, $20,000-to-win Outlaw finale for big-block modifieds. As many as 50 modifieds are expected to run in qualifying heats, which start at 4:30.
Late models also were part of Friday night's show, with Bryce Davis picking up $1,000 for winning a 50-lap feature event.
Bret Belden and Kevan Cook finished second and third.
Joe Isabell earned $1,000 for winning the Doug Cooper Memorial Event for mod lites. He was followed by Jim Bogett and Joe Garafolo in the 36-lap race.
